Cell[TextData[{
 "A microwave oven functions by dielectric heating of water molecules and \
other polar compounds, usually proteins in food. The alternating electric \
field of the microwave radiation, commonly at a frequency of 2.45 GHz, causes \
rapid reorientation of the polar molecules, generating heat by frictional \
interactions with neighboring molecules. The water molecules ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   GraphicsBox[
    TagBox[RasterBox[CompressedData["
1:eJztmL9rIkEUxweuD2yTxjRXhiBpAqYJe4HrhIDCEbSJp9VaqK3CgXDKgZYp
5KqrvCvuX0h1f4GCV6TONimCFgcnKux9dIIkxrg/fMYL7Je3yzI7+/Y77715
b2beZovJ7BulVJQrxjV9dkKEeD2YTCadTqfVapVKpVwux51nWmjfNrV7DIfD
er2eyWQsy6pUKtVqlTvPtNRqtX6/v22CzmAwiMfjqVSqugzZbJa3jGKLDPEm
toLJUoYa6XSaPoH9vn4g0RmfrmCoQR96BmAoEkgMik9cSdKHnn4ZSgUSxi+X
y64kGX6hUOh2uz+azS9nZ83j46/R6Lf9fe4800I7b0ej0VyzYCARJK4MNd4f
HX2PRHpK/aW8PhZaaOdtM5H4dXU1Ho8d0UDybkkrEnGe0FuQO6V+7u5e5vO2
bQsGkg9VOzuuJLVcK9U8PcXRHoePoVaT9OoU0+x4Y6jFVurdwYGrWg1CbjVJ
Hd4E8Aol2YuLumFM/JBErL09KUs6s1RGKnhuGqbPz+OG0ffJECE8ZJMbCQ17
6pSrh899mnJNs2YYQ/8MEcKDz11J+ioT8+JVLBbJNvlIBFPwI79engsfMkAc
sYIh7qMeBSi45OS2h2zjRXABofLxmYnJRCDMgi2xqB09CYZaBkqVDONDMrkY
SLPaHXhxRY17WlPWkT9KFUxTdjndiMUEGWqhvgfmsxSsGcRJTnWKgrWNOMmp
TlG8Cks2iJ//PibFZzfa0ClLUjZPOrP1MDplSQpWHC2s2NEpS5LFfyORuBNi
iB72FA/3PlJgn8IuQIQketAmztCZGfPSsq7XZogG9jt6X7YJsJP6fHJyuwZD
e7bTQc+GGN7zvLn5dHhoB2LI6Pj2d6+3UYYa/AVr+PU7/fECY3wBhhr4i/gk
/r3M94f77hdjqEHkM0PJS+2VJxjtxycYWwG/np8FseacnwXxvPQsKESIECEW
8A+9bb3h
      "], {{0, 45}, {55, 0}}, {0, 255},
      ColorFunction->RGBColor],
     BoxForm`ImageTag["Byte", ColorSpace -> "RGB", Interleaving -> True],
     Selectable->False],
    BaseStyle->"ImageGraphics",
    ImageSize->{36., Automatic},
    ImageSizeRaw->{55, 45},
    PlotRange->{{0, 55}, {0, 45}}], TraditionalForm]], "InlineMath"],
 "are highly magnified relative to the large organic molecules for better \
visualization of their oscillations. The microwave oven turns itself off when \
the contents are sufficiently heated. Doesn't that protein molecule look \
yummy!"
}], "Text"]
}, Close]]
}, Open  ]],

